---
const withBase = (path: string) => {
  const base = '/arcup';
  if (path === '/') return `${base}/`;
  return `${base}${path}`;
};
---

<main id="main-content" class="page-shell page-why-clean" aria-labelledby="why-title">
  
  <!-- HERO -->
  <header class="why-hero-clean" aria-labelledby="why-title">
    <p class="hero-eyebrow">the answer to "why we need arc^"</p>
    <h1 id="why-title" class="hero-question">
      what if the next big breakthrough<br />was built in the open?
    </h1>
    <p class="hero-subquestion">
      in that world, what future would your novel idea create?
    </p>
    <p class="hero-origin">
      arc^ began from that question. not as a product idea, but from a moment of reflection.
    </p>
  </header>

  <!-- SECTION 1: THE PROBLEM -->
  <section class="section-problem-clean" aria-labelledby="problem-heading">
    <div class="section-container">
      
      <h2 id="problem-heading" class="section-title">what's the problem?</h2>

      <div class="problem-questions">
        <p class="question-italic">if i follow the same path as the past</p>
        <p class="question-italic">and if everyone does the same</p>
        <p class="question-italic">will we ever reach the futures we hope for?</p>
      </div>

      <p class="narrative-lead">i looked backward and saw a pattern:</p>

      <!-- Pattern Visual - Mobile Optimized -->
      <div class="pattern-simple">
        <span class="pattern-word">conflict</span>
        <span class="pattern-arrow" aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="arrow-desktop">→</span>
          <span class="arrow-mobile">↓</span>
        </span>
        <span class="pattern-word">production</span>
        <span class="pattern-arrow" aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="arrow-desktop">→</span>
          <span class="arrow-mobile">↓</span>
        </span>
        <span class="pattern-word">patents</span>
        <span class="pattern-arrow" aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="arrow-desktop">→</span>
          <span class="arrow-mobile">↓</span>
        </span>
        <span class="pattern-word">profit</span>
        <span class="pattern-arrow" aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="arrow-desktop">→</span>
          <span class="arrow-mobile">↓</span>
        </span>
        <span class="pattern-word">power</span>
        <span class="pattern-arrow pattern-arrow-harm" aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="arrow-desktop">→</span>
          <span class="arrow-mobile">↓</span>
        </span>
        <span class="pattern-word pattern-word-harm">harm</span>
      </div>

      <p class="pattern-caption">
        a repeating cycle of violence, materialism, and extraction. dressed up as progress.
      </p>

      <!-- Today's Reality -->
      <div class="today-block">
        <p class="today-label">today that loop looks like:</p>
        <ul class="today-list">
          <li>curiosity gated by funding.</li>
          <li>discovery delayed for the market.</li>
          <li>scale that replaces meaning.</li>
          <li>top-down incentives overriding truths of practice.</li>
          <li>science run as strategy, not as a humble search for knowledge.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- The Cost -->
      <div class="cost-block-t-shape">
        <div class="t-shape-top">
          <div class="t-left">
            <p class="consequence-text">
              our best ideas are dying waiting for approval from systems that no longer serve us.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="t-right">
            <p class="wait-line">we wait.</p>
            <p class="wait-line">we delay.</p>
            <p class="wait-line">we privatize.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="t-bottom">
          <p class="cost-text">
            and it <strong>has cost us dearly:</strong> exploited people, collapsing ecosystems, fractured communities, polarization, and futures that are becoming harder to inherit.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- The Refusal -->
      <div class="refusal-block">
        <p class="refusal-statement">
          arc^ refuses to copy/paste the old playbook.<br />
          it doesn't work. it won't get us where we must go.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 2: THE DECISION -->
  <section class="section-decision" aria-labelledby="decision-heading">
    <div class="section-container">
      
      <h2 id="decision-heading" class="section-title">what's the decision?</h2>

      <div class="decision-questions">
        <p class="question-italic">what if the most ambitious goals—our most outlandish visions—were grounded in accountability?</p>
        <p class="question-italic">what if responsibility—not secrecy, not profit—defined innovation?</p>
      </div>

      <div class="decision-definition">
        <p>
          arc^ is not a brand. It's not a product. It's not a lab that will magically "save the world."
        </p>
        <p class="definition-emphasis">
          <strong>arc^ is a decision about how we want to be human together:</strong> science as philosophy, praxis, and partnership.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="decision-meaning">
        <p>
          We choose to build in the open, because outdated frameworks that protect work by locking it away are causing harm.
        </p>
        <p>
          We design with repair in mind. We are responsible to collective goals—the goals of the many—and we measure everything by their consequences on people, ecosystems, and future generations.
        </p>
        <p class="decision-core">
          <strong>We operate to minimize harm and maximize repair.</strong>
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- RE:TECH Brief Intro -->
      <div class="retech-brief">
        <h3>RE:TECH: our design posture</h3>
        <p class="retech-tagline">Refuse Extractive Technology.</p>
        <p>
          If a tool, process, or system extracts, exploits, or restricts repair and restoration—we do not build it.
        </p>

        <div class="retech-principles-brief">
          <div class="principle-brief">
            <h4>transparent</h4>
            <p>not hidden behind NDAs and patents</p>
          </div>
          <div class="principle-brief">
            <h4>collaborative</h4>
            <p>not competitive and extractive</p>
          </div>
          <div class="principle-brief">
            <h4>regenerative</h4>
            <p>not extractive and destructive</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="retech-learn-more">
          <a href={withBase("/how")}>See how RE:TECH guides our work →</a>
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 3: THE VISION -->
  <section class="section-vision" aria-labelledby="vision-heading">
    <div class="section-container">
      
      <h2 id="vision-heading" class="section-title">what do we build?</h2>

      <div class="vision-intro">
        <h3>open infrastructure for collective repair.</h3>
        <p>
          arc^ builds the tools, protocols, templates, and living prototypes that let ambitious science happen in public—without exploiting people or the planet.
        </p>
        <p>
          We want discovery to belong to many, not to a privileged few, and to make sure scale is bound to consent and repair.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- What We're Building -->
      <div class="building-block">
        <h4>living, growing, evolving products—not polished patented barriers</h4>
        <p>
          We publish early and deliberately: prototypes, experiment notebooks, versioned protocols, modular components that others can adopt, test, and extend.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our goal is <strong>reproducible momentum</strong>, not a private patent that sits on a shelf.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Core Goals -->
      <div class="goals-block">
        <h4>core goals</h4>
        <ul class="goals-list">
          <li>Rebuild safe, open plasma technologies: modular, documented, replicable.</li>
          <li>Release hardware blueprints and DBD reactor components as community assets.</li>
          <li>Create a public library (ArcIndex) of open protocols, templates, and community solutions.</li>
          <li>Produce governance templates and consent frameworks for community-led research.</li>
          <li>Help regenerative, local solutions scale ethically—not extractively.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Research Areas -->
      <div class="research-areas">
        <h4>research areas</h4>
        <div class="research-grid-clean">
          <div class="research-item">
            <h5>Open Plasma Systems</h5>
            <p>Modular plasma-reactor designs, safety-first, reproducible in community labs.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="research-item">
            <h5>DBD Components & Hardware</h5>
            <p>Open blueprints for dielectric-barrier discharge components and build guides.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="research-item">
            <h5>Salt & Water Systems</h5>
            <p>Research on low-cost, regenerative irrigation and saline-adapted solutions.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="research-item">
            <h5>Remediation & Restoration</h5>
            <p>Protocols for soil, water, and air remediation using scalable, community-deployable tech.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="research-item">
            <h5>Human & Environmental Health</h5>
            <p>Open studies focused on measurable, community-centered health outcomes.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="research-item">
            <h5>Reproducibility Tooling</h5>
            <p>Tests, CI scripts, and notebooks to make experiments repeatable by anyone.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Success Vision -->
      <div class="success-vision">
        <h3>if we succeed</h3>
        <p>
          We'll host a public library of community solutions—hardware blueprints, protocols, templates—and a set of tested case studies that let local projects replicate and adapt without gatekeepers.
        </p>
        <p class="success-goal">
          <strong>Our biggest goal:</strong> shift our relationship with technology so that it supports humanity's repair and flourishing.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FINAL CTA -->
  <section class="closing-cta">
    <div class="section-container">
      <p class="closing-statement">
        arc^ builds <strong>open infrastructure for collective repair</strong>—tools, knowledge, and networks that reject the extractive paradigm.
      </p>
      <p class="closing-question">
        ready to see how this works in practice?
      </p>
      <div class="closing-buttons">
        <a href={withBase("/how")} class="button button-large">Explore How We Work</a>
        <a href={withBase("/projects")} class="button button-outline button-large">Browse Projects</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</main>

<footer class="site-footer">
  <div class="footer-content">
    <p class="footer-text">
      arc^ by ali · collaborative research for planetary repair
    </p>
    <p class="footer-license">
      <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">CC BY-NC-SA</a> · 
      <a href="https://ohwr.org/cern_ohl_s_v2.txt" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">CERN OHL-S</a> · 
      <a href="https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.en.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">AGPL-3.0</a>
    </p>
  </div>
  <button type="button" data-motion-toggle class="button button-muted">Disable Motion</button>
</footer>

<style>
  /* Additional styles for new/modified sections */
  
  /* Decision Section */
  .section-decision {
    padding: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 4rem) 0;
  }

  .decision-questions {
    display: grid;
    gap: clamp(0.75rem, 2vw, 1rem);
    margin-bottom: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
  }

  .decision-definition {
    margin: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem) 0;
    padding: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.25rem);
    background: rgba(6, 12, 22, 0.5);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-primary-bright);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .decision-definition p {
    margin: 0 0 clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.25rem) 0;
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 2.5vw, 1.15rem);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .decision-definition p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .definition-emphasis strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .decision-meaning {
    margin: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem) 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 1.75rem);
  }

  .decision-meaning p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 2.5vw, 1.15rem);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .decision-core {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: rgba(10, 147, 150, 0.12);
    border: 1px solid rgba(93, 225, 228, 0.3);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .decision-core strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2.8vw, 1.3rem);
  }

  /* RE:TECH Brief */
  .retech-brief {
    margin: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 4rem) 0;
    padding: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
    background: rgba(6, 12, 22, 0.4);
    border: 1px solid rgba(93, 225, 228, 0.2);
    border-radius: 12px;
  }

  .retech-brief h3 {
    margin: 0 0 clamp(0.75rem, 2vw, 1rem) 0;
    font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 3.8vw, 1.7rem);
    color: var(--color-primary-bright);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .retech-tagline {
    margin: 0 0 clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.5rem) 0;
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2.8vw, 1.3rem);
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .retech-brief > p {
    margin: 0 0 clamp(1.5rem, 3.5vw, 2rem) 0;
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 2.5vw, 1.15rem);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .retech-principles-brief {
    display: grid;
    gap: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 1.5rem);
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(min(200px, 100%), 1fr));
    margin-bottom: clamp(1.5rem, 3.5vw, 2rem);
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .retech-principles-brief {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }
  }

  .principle-brief {
    padding: clamp(1.5rem, 3.5vw, 1.75rem);
    background: rgba(8, 15, 27, 0.6);
    border: 1px solid rgba(93, 225, 228, 0.2);
    border-radius: 10px;
    text-align: center;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .principle-brief:hover {
    border-color: rgba(93, 225, 228, 0.4);
    transform: translateY(-3px);
  }

  .principle-brief h4 {
    margin: 0 0 clamp(0.5rem, 1.5vw, 0.75rem) 0;
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2.8vw, 1.25rem);
    color: var(--color-primary-bright);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .principle-brief p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(0.95rem, 2.2vw, 1.05rem);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .retech-learn-more {
    margin: 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .retech-learn-more a {
    color: var(--color-primary-bright);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 2.5vw, 1.15rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(93, 225, 228, 0.3);
    transition: border-color var(--transition-base);
  }

  .retech-learn-more a:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-primary-bright);
  }

  /* Vision Section */
  .section-vision {
    padding: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 4rem) 0;
  }

  .vision-intro {
    margin-bottom: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 4rem);
  }

  .vision-intro h3 {
    margin: 0 0 clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.5rem) 0;
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 1.9rem);
    color: var(--color-primary-bright);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .vision-intro p {
    margin: 0 0 clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.25rem) 0;
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 2.5vw, 1.15rem);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .vision-intro p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .building-block,
  .goals-block,
  .research-areas {
    margin: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 3.5rem) 0;
  }

  .building-block h4,
  .goals-block h4,
  .research-areas h4 {
    margin: 0 0 clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.25rem) 0;
    font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 3.2vw, 1.4rem);
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .building-block p {
    margin: 0 0 clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.25rem) 0;
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 2.5vw, 1.15rem);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .building-block p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Closing CTA */
  .closing-cta {
    padding: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 4rem) 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .closing-statement {
    margin: 0 0 clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem) 0;
    font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 3vw, 1.35rem);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .closing-statement strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .closing-question {
    margin: 0 0 clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem) 0;
    font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 3.2vw, 1.5rem);
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .closing-buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .closing-buttons {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: stretch;
    }
    
    .closing-buttons .button {
      width: 100%;
    }
  }
</style>
